fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.computers

Class ComputerStaticState

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.computers.ComputerStaticState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI, ComputerStaticStateI, TimeStampingI, java.io.Serializable

    public class ComputerStaticState
extends java.lang.Object
implements ComputerStaticStateI
    The class ComputerStaticState implements objects representing a snapshot of the static state of a computer component to be pulled or pushed through the static state data interface.

    Description

    Invariant

    TDOO: complete! 
     invariant              timestamp >= 0 && timestamperIP != null
 invariant              computerURI != null
 invariant              numberOfProcessors > 0
 invariant              numberOfCoresPerProcessor > 0
 invariant              processorURIs != null && processorURIs.size() == numberOfProcessors
 invariant              processorsPortURIs != null
 invariant              processorsPortURIs.keySet().size() == numberOfProcessors

    Created on : April 14, 2015

    Version:
    $Name$ -- $Revision$ -- $Date$

    Jacques Malenfant

        public ComputerStaticState(java.lang.String computerURI,
                           int numberOfProcessors,
                           int numberOfCoresPerProcessor,
                           java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> processorURIs,
                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.Map<Processor.ProcessorPortTypes,java.lang.String>> processorsPortURIs)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        create a static state snapshot.

        Contract

         pre    computerURI != null
 pre    numberOfProcessors > 0
 pre    numberOfCoresPerProcessor > 0
 pre    processorURIs != null && processorURIs.size() == numberOfProcessors
 pre    processorsPortURIs != null
 pre    processorsPortURIs.keySet().size() == numberOfProcessors
 post   true                    // no postcondition.
        Parameters:
        computerURI - URI of the computer to which this static state relates.
        numberOfProcessors - number of processors owned by the computer.
        numberOfCoresPerProcessor - number of cores per processors owned by the computer.
        processorURIs - map between processor numbers and their URI.
        processorsPortURIs - map between processor URI and their different ports URI.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
